- Web component is a spec. They are just vanillq JS with no dependencies. Easily re-usable.
1) Custom HTML: They are custom HTML elements is part of the spec.This helps you register your own html tags.
2) Shadow DOM: Manage a separate DOM node tree for your HTML elements (including scoped CSS styles)
3) Templates and slots: Write HTML templates that you can add to your HTML elements.
4) HTML imports spec: Importing HTML files [Not continued]

- It helps us encapsulate logic and UI. That helps in reusability. Easy to understand and maintain
Separation of concerns. Publish as NPM package.

- Component driven approaches in all places.


